<item>
            <title>[HIVE-5104] HCatStorer fails to store boolean type</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HIVE-5104</link>
                <project id="12310843" key="HIVE">Hive</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Unable to store boolean values to HCat table &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Assume in Hive you have two tables...&lt;br/&gt;
CREATE TABLE btest(test as boolean);&lt;br/&gt;
CREATE TABLE btest2(test as boolean);&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Then in Pig &lt;br/&gt;
A = LOAD &apos;btest&apos; USING org.apache.hcatalog.pig.HCatLoader();&lt;br/&gt;
STORE A INTO &apos;btest2&apos; USING org.apache.hcatalog.pig.HCatStorer();&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;You will get an &quot;ERROR 115: Unsupported type 5: in Pig&apos;s Schema&quot;  &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Checking HCatBaseStorer.java, the case for data types doesn&apos;t check for booleans.  Might have been overlooked in adding boolean to Pig in 0.10&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
